items.checkin_comment: One a day historical check in, drank June 2011 @The Grape & Grain, Crystal Palace. Lemon, ginger and fresh herb aromas. Ginger, heather and light spice flavours. Dry, fruity finish.

items.badge_description: Want to enjoy a day of brews, but need to keep your wits sharp? There are plenty of delicious brews under 5% for you to sip on throughout the day. That's 50 different beers with an ABV of 5% and lower. Try 5 more for Level 11!

While a pint of traditional English ale will always remain a staple, the craft beer scene in England, much like the rest of the world, has continued to grow at a rapid rate! That's 20 different beers from a brewery from England! Try 5 more for Level 5!
